<HEADLINE> HK to Host 1st Men's Asian Hockey Federation Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 19 (Xinhua) -- The inaugural Men's Asian
Hockey Federation Cup will be held in Hong Kong from November 22
to 30, organizers announced here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Sanctioned by the International Hockey Federation and the Asian
Hockey Federation, the tournament is jointly organized by the Hong
Kong Hockey Association and the Provisional Urban Council with
sponsorship from the Hong Kong Sports Development Board.
</P>
<P>
Competing in the tournament will be teams from Chinese Taipei,
Oman, Singapore, Macao, Uzbekistan, Sri Lanka and hosts Hong Kong,
China.
</P>
<P>
The tournament is the third major hockey competition in Asia,
following the existing tournaments of the Asian Games and the
Asian Cup.
</P>
<P>
The event will adopt single round robin system and the winner
team will be invited to the Asian Cup in 1999.
</P>
<P>
The first Women's Asian Hockey Federation Cup is slated for
December 4-14 in Singapore, with teams from Chinese Taipei,
Malaysia, Kazakhistan,
Sri Lanka, Thailand, Singapore and Hong Kong, China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
