<HEADLINE> Angola, Sweden Sign Cooperation Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, November 19 (Xinhua) -- The governments of Angola and
Sweden signed here today three agreements of cooperation and
renewed another two to strengthen the existing friedly and
cooperation ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The three new cooperation agreements are centered on a
training program for strengthening government abilities of
formulating economic and social policies, a humanitarian
assistance project and a social assistance fund respectively.
</P>
<P>
The agreements were inked by Angolan Foreign Minister Sebasuao
Isata and Swedish ambassador to Angola Zena Sunch on behalf of
their governments respectively.
</P>
<P>
The existing agreements of fishery and telecommunications
cooperation and energy cooperation between the two countries
were also extended to December, 1999 on the same occasion.
</P>
