<HEADLINE> Sha Zukang to Participate Geneva Meeting on Iraq Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Ambassador Sha Zukang at
China's permanent mission in Geneva will take part in a
ministerial meeting to end the three-week-old Iraq weapons
inspection crisis peacefully, diplomatic sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
Sha will join British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook, French
Foreign Minister Hubert Vedrine, Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny
Primakov and US Secretary of State Madeleine Albright for the
meeting expected at about 3 am Geneva time on Thursday in the
Geneva International Airport.
</P>
<P>
Russia, which initiated the meeting, is keeping their proposal
secret until the meeting begins. The Russian proposal is said to
contain a solution to the crisis without force and reaffirming the
authority of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
China, France, Russia, the United Kingdom and the United States
are the five permanent members of the Security Council and each
has the right to veto decisions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
