<HEADLINE> Pak PM Urges President to Sign Bill into Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif today urged President Farooq Leghari to sign the
Amended Contempt of Court Bill into law to end the prevailing
political crisis in the country.
</P>
<P>
"Earlier the bill is signed, sooner the crisis will come to an
end. The country has not suffered the damage in the last 25 years
as it regrettably has in the last two weeks," said Sharif.
</P>
<P>
Talking to the media after chairing the Parliamentary meeting
of the Pakistan Muslim League (N) and its allied parties at the
Parliament House, Sharif said the present uncertainty has
adversely affected Pakistan in all spheres of life.
</P>
<P>
"The situation is pushing the country to the brink of
destruction," the prime minister added.
</P>
<P>
"There is a contempt of court case against me and the decision
can come any time, so it is imperative that the Bill which has
been passed by the two houses of the Parliament be signed, and we
can defend ourselves," said Sharif.
</P>
<P>
He also said that Pakistan is passing through extra-ordinary
situation which calls for an early signing of the bill by the head
of state.  
</P>
</TEXT>
