<DOCNO> XIE19971120.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France to Use Public Research Fund to Innovate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 19 (Xinhua) -- The French government will use
public research fund to help innovate small enterprises first,
instead of big enterprises, said French Minister of National
Education, Research and Technology Claude Allegre today.
</P>
<P>
"The government is Socialist and realist. We hope to support
the creation of innovating small and medium-sized enterprises,"
said Allegre at the "Bio Avenir"seminar hosted by the
Rhone-Poulenc chemical and pharmaceutical corporation of France.
</P>
<P>
The international seminar was focused on a biological research
program staged over the past five years by the corporation and
several state institutions, which cost Rhone-Poulenc 1.6 billion
francs (270 million U.S. dollars), according to the president of
Rhone-Poulenc, Jean-Rene Fourtou.
</P>
<P>
Allegre said that the government will offer financial support
to young people with doctorate degrees to head innovation projects
in small enterprises, as part of its plan to create 350,000 jobs
for the young people.
</P>
<P>
He also suggested that France abandon what he called
"excessive ethic purism" in the field of biological research.
</P>
<P>
"We will not ban the French from researches on trans-genetic
corn, while importing at the same time from the United States
trans-genetic corn," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
