<HEADLINE> France Ready to Fill Out Presence in UNSCOM in Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 19 (Xinhua) -- France said today that it is
ready to fill out its presence in the United Nations special
commission on arms inspection in Iraq (UNSCOM), if it is asked to
provide supplementary personnel in the mission.
</P>
<P>
"It is up to the special commission on disarmament of Iraq to
analyze the situation. If it asks us to do more, we will examine
this request with benevolence," said French Foreign Ministry
spokeswoman Anne Gazeau-Secret.
</P>
<P>
The question of reshaping the UNSCOM will be discussed by the
foreign ministers of the United States, Britain, France and Russia
in Geneva this evening and in New York on Friday at the U.N.
Security Council.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers of the four nations will also discuss the
layout of the U.N. resolution on "oil for food" program for Iraq
in order to let Iraq obtain more humanitarian goods for its
civilians, the progress made in the disarmament of Iraq's nuclear,
ballistic, chemical and biological weapons, and a harmonization of
positions among the members of the U.N. Security Council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
