<HEADLINE> Arafat Meets Peres on Economic Aid to PNA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) President Yasser Arafat held talks today with
former Israeli Prime Minister Shimon Peres in Gaza to discuss
economic aid to the PNA.
</P>
<P>
According to local reports, Arafat described his meeting with
Peres as "important and constructive," during which they also
discussed the latest political developments in the Middle
East.
</P>
<P>
Peres briefed Arafat on his meeting last week with United
States President Bill Clinton in Washington.
</P>
<P>
Peres, who founded the Peres Center for Peace last month to
promote regional peace through economic projects, has just
returned from Qatari capital Doha where he attended the annual
Middle East and North Africa economic conference.
</P>
<P>
He said he would help improve the living standard of
Palestinians and would introduce morden technologies to the
Palestinian territories to help improve the their economy.
</P>
<P>
In his speech to the Doha conference, Peres expressed hope that
Palestinian people would enjoy peace and prosperity, because a
better Palestinian state would be a better neighbor to Israel.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after his meeting with Peres, Arafat departed for
his visit to India, which is aimed at strengthening bilateral
economic relations. 
</P>
