<HEADLINE> Geneva Meeting on Iraq to Be Held in Palais des Nations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, November 19 (Xinhua) -- The meeting aimed to end the
Iraq weapons inspection crisis peacefully will be held at 2 am on
Thursday in the Council Chamber at the Palais des Nations, the
United Nations Office in Geneva (UNOG) announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The ministers attending the meeting are British Foreign
Secretary Robin Cook, French Foreign Minister Hubert Vedrine,
Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov and US Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Sha Zukang at China's permanent mission in Geneva
will take part in a ministerial meeting to end the three-week-old
Iraq weapons inspection crisis peacefully, said a spokesman at the
mission.
</P>
<P>
Russia, which initiated the meeting, is keeping their proposal
secret until the meeting begins. The Russian proposal is said to
contain a solution to the crisis without force and reaffirming the
authority of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
China, France, Russia, the United Kingdom and the United States
are the five permanent members of the Security Council and each
has the right to veto decisions. 
</P>
