<HEADLINE> 16 People Killed in Landslide in Southern </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Sixteen persons were
killed and 10 others injured by landslide which followed heavy
rains in Arba-Minch, southern Ethiopia last week, the Ethiopian
News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted a local official Amaru Wale as saying that
the remains of nine of the deceased were discovered 15 kilometers
away from their residential quarters where the accident happened.
</P>
<P>
The official said the bodies of the other seven persons have
not been found so far.
</P>
<P>
He said the landslide has also destroyed seven residential
units and crops on 20 hectares of land in the reported area.
</P>
<P>
There is a plan to resettle the 2,000 people living along the
mountain which had been hit by the landslide, according to the
official. 
</P>
