<HEADLINE> Market Share Gap Narrows Between Airbus, Boeing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 19 (Xinhua) - The battle for greater world
market share between Airbus and Boeing intensified as the European
Group beat its US rival to land a one billion pounds (1.6 billion
US dollars) deal recently.
</P>
<P>
The reported order for 34 aircraft from Belgian flag-carrier
Sabena will close the gap in this year's fight for market share
between the world's two wide-bodied aircraft makers.
</P>
<P>
The market has traditionally been split two thirds / one third
in the American group's favor though last year Airbus won nearly
40 percent.
</P>
<P>
But at the end of October Airbus had booked orders this year
for 425 aircraft against 469 for Boeing.
</P>
<P>
An Airbus spokesman said on Tuesday: "We are catching up, we
are getting above the 40 percent of 1996, we are getting even
closer to 50/50." 
</P>
