<HEADLINE> Prince Philip Says Tolerance is Secret of Happy Marriage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 19 (Xinhua) -- The Duke of Edinburgh Prince
Philip said today the secret of keeping a successful marriage
between him and Queen Elizabeth over the past 50 years was
tolerance.
</P>
<P>
"The main lesson that we have learnt is that tolerance is the
one essential ingredient of any happy marriage," Prince Philip
said at a banquet on the eve of the Queen and the Duke's 50th
wedding anniversary.
</P>
<P>
It may not be quite so important when things are going well,
but it is absolutely vital when the going gets difficult, he said,
adding: "You can take it from that the Queen has the quality of
tolerance in abundance."
</P>
<P>
In his speech, the Duke also praised his children, saying "our
children have all done rather well under very difficult and
demanding circumstances and I hope I can be forgiven for feeling
proud of them."
</P>
<P>
Four former prime ministers--Baroness Thatcher, John Major,
Lord Callaghan, and Sir Edward Heath--were among VIP guests at
today's banquet in London.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, the Queen will give her Golden Wedding speech at a
celebration lunch hosted by Prime Minister Tony Blair. 
