<DOCNO> XIE19971120.0053 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IDB Helps Ecuador, Peru Combat El Nino Phenomenon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 19 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of a 255
million U.S. dollars to help Ecuador and Peru combat the El Nino
climate phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
The El Nino phenomenon could cause abnormal flooding and
fisheries losses in Ecuador and northern Peru as well as drought
in southern Peru.
</P>
<P>
Under the arrangement, the IDB is providing a 150 million
dollar loan to Peru, and 105 million dollars to Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
The resources will be utilized for humanitarian disaster aid,
public works, agricultural projects, planning and administration,
clean up, protection of building and historic monuments, and
relocation of communities to higher ground.
</P>
<P>
Financial assistance from the IDB, the World Bank and the
Andean Development Corporation in dealing with the
damaging effects of El Nino in the two Latin American nations is
expected to reach 510 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
