<HEADLINE> Philippine House Approves Budget on Final Reading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 20 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine House of
Representatives today approved on third and final reading the
540.8 billion pesos (15.5 billion U.S. dollars) 1998 budget.
</P>
<P>
House Speaker Jose de Venecia described the bill as a "landmark
bill" and unprecedented for its socio-economic-building features
as the country makes its way into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The House approval of the budget is right on schedule as the
bill should be signed into law before Christmas and become
effective by January 1, 1998, according to the speaker.
</P>
<P>
The House put budget priority on education, appropriating 80.8
billion pesos (2.3 billion dollars), followed by the Department of
National Defense with 50.9 billion pesos (1.5 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
Under the 1998 budget, 1 billion pesos subsidy will be
allocated to raise the salaries of the country's 150,000 private
school teachers as assistance to private schools and help them
reach the increasing salary rate of public school teachers.
</P>
