<HEADLINE> MagneTek Opens Hong Kong Branch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 20 (Xinhua) -- U.S-based MagneTek, a
multinational manufacturer of integrated electrical products, has
opened its Asia branch in Hong Kong, according to Ronald Hoge, the
company's president and chief executive officer.
</P>
<P>
Hoge announced establishment of the branch at today's session
of the '97 International Symposium of Electronic Ballasts
sponsored by the China Green Lights Program.
</P>
<P>
MagneTek hopes to further explore the Asian market by using
China as its sales, R&AMP;D and manufacturing base, according to Hoge.
</P>
<P>
He said the company supports and will be actively involved in
the ongoing China Green Lights Program, a key national energy
conservation project designed to promote the efficient use of
energy and related products.
</P>
<P>
"MagneTek is excited to be a partner in China's endeavors to
increase efficient energy consumption and looks forward to using
its technology to assist the nation in energy conservation
efforts," said Hoge.
</P>
<P>
The company plans to invest in an electronic ballast production
plant in China, said Hoge, noting that ballasts are a key
component of lighting systems.
</P>
<P>
MagneTek and a local company have previously established a
generator production plant in Fuzhou, capital of the coastal
Fujian Province. The joint venture, established at a cost of 10.5
million US dollars, went into operation early this year and has an
annual production capacity of 8,500 generators.
</P>
<P>
Bernard Kwok, president of MagneTek Asia Inc., said the parent
company has fully exhibited its confidence in the Chinese market
by establishing its Asia branch in Hong Kong. MagneTek plans to
invest a total of 20 million US dollars in Asia over the next
three years, with the major portion of funds earmarked for
expanding its production and sales network in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
