<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Funeral for Former Deputy Chief of PLA General Staff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 20 (Xinhua) -- The remains of Wu Xiuquan,
former deputy chief of General Staff of the Chinese People's
Liberation Army (PLA), were cremated today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Senior government and Party leaders paying their respects
included Chinese President Jiang Zemin, Qiao Shi, Zhu Rongji, Liu
Huaqing, Hu Jingtao and Wei Jianxing.
</P>
<P>
Wu, 90, who served a standing committee member of the former
CPC Advisory Commission, died on November 9, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Ambassadors and dignitaries from countries throughout the world
including Russia, Japan, the Republic of Korea, Poland, Germany
and the United States sent letters of condolence to the Chinese
government and Wu's family.
</P>
<P>
Wu graduated from the Moscow Infantry School in the former
Soviet Union and joined the Communist Party of China and Red Army
in 1931. Wu participated in the Long March (1934-1935) and
thereafter served in the leadership of China's revolutionary
military forces.
</P>
<P>
He became deputy chief of the PLA General Staff in 1975, and
served as a delegate to the seventh, eighth, eleventh and
fourteenth CPC national congresses. He was also a member of
the eighth and eleventh CPC Central Committees.
</P>
<P>
Wu was also invited to serve as a special delegate to the 15th
CPC National Congress held in Beijing in September this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971120.0069 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> "People's Daily" Editorial Urges Further Financial Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 20 (Xinhua) -- An editorial in tomorrow's
edition of "People's Daily" calls for creating a new situation in
the reform of China's financial system.
</P>
<P>
The highly important national financial conference which ended
in Beijing on Wednesday will have far-reaching significance in
promoting China's reforms and socialist modernization, as well as
in achieving trans-century objectives, according to the editorial.
</P>
<P>
Tangible achievements recorded in financial supervision and
services over the past few years have played a major role in
strengthening macroeconomic control, accelerating economic growth
and maintaining social stability.
</P>
<P>
Facts prove that the principles and policies adopted by the
Party Central Committee and State Council are correct and
effective, according to the editorial.
</P>
<P>
However, it noted that a number of problems, including an
incomplete legal system, lax management over finances and
violations of the law and financial disciplines by some financial
institutions continue to exist.
</P>
<P>
"We should pay special attention and promptly introduce
measures to solve related problems," stressed the editorial.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the financial conference was to promote the
establishment of a financial system by deepening reform and
enhancing supervision in order to legalize financial activities
and minimize financial risks.
</P>
<P>
China enjoys a relatively good macroeconomic situation, rapid
and sustained economic growth, stable prices, ample grain supplies
and substantial foreign exchange reserves.
</P>
<P>
"We should make full use of all favorable conditions to expand
financial reforms and solve financial problems left over from
history," according to the editorial.  
</P>
</TEXT>
