<HEADLINE> Employment to Top EU Summit Agenda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LUXEMBOURG, November 20 (Xinhua) -- The issue of employment is
to top the agenda of the two-day European Union (EU) summit
beginning here today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will assess the progress the bloc's 15 member
states have made in this field and discuss ways for further
improvement.
</P>
<P>
The Employment Policy Guidelines, agreed upon in Amsterdam in
June, set some quantifiable targets for the members.
</P>
<P>
The degree of attainment of these targets will be monitored
and examined by the European Commission, the EU's executive body,
on the basis of the reports submitted by the member states.
</P>
<P>
The EU's mid-1997 unemployment rate was 10.6 percent. In 1996,
over 5 percent of its labor force was without jobs. 
</P>
