<HEADLINE> Longest Cableway in Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, November 20 (Xinhua) -- A 3,709-meter cableway,
reportedly the longest in Asia, entered trial operations today in
the Huangshan Mountain Tourist Zone.
</P>
<P>
The longest span of the cableway, which spans three canyons,
stretches 1,513 meters. Six towers support the system which rises
to an elevation of 1,014 meters.
</P>
<P>
Each carriage accommodates 101 passengers and requires eight
minutes to complete a circuit.
</P>
<P>
The cableway was designed by the Beijing Nonferrous Metallurgy
Design and Research Institute, and was constructed at a cost of
152 million yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
