<DOCNO> XIE19971120.0077 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-20 14:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Aziz: UNSCOM Can Resume Work in Iraq From Now </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi Deputy Premier Tariq Aziz
said today the U.N. Special Commission (UNSCOM) entrusted with
ridding Iraq of weapons of mass destruction can resume its mission
as of now.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference after his talks with Arab League
(AL) Secretary General Esmat Abdel Meguid at the AL headquarters,
Aziz said Baghdad declares its approval of the return of all
members of the UNSCOM to carry out their task without any
conditions on the represented nationalities.
</P>
<P>
It was decided following the exchanged messages between Russian
President Boris Yeltsin and Iraqi President Saddam Hussein, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Aziz said Russia was committed to exerting genuine efforts to
lift the sanctions imposed after Iraq's invasion of Kuwait in
1990, and (ensuring) the UNSCOM respect of the sovereignty of Iraq.
</P>
<P>
"Iraq is thus giving a chance for a political and diplomatic
solution to lift the Security Council-imposed embargo," he said.
</P>
<P>
However, he warned that should the United States continue to
neglect the Iraqi legitimate rights and obstructed correcting the
position of the UNSCOM there will be "another attitude."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the U.N. inspection teams in charge of scrapping
Iraqi weapons of mass destruction will return to Baghdad within
hours.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, the Iraqi National Council accepted a Russian
proposal to allow all the U.N. arms inspectors, including the
Americans, to come back immediately to renew their monitoring of
its weapons systems.
</P>
<P>
Iraq and Russia also agreed that Russia will work for the
lifting of the crippling seven-year-old economic sanctions.
</P>
<P>
Iraq's decision ends the standoff which saw an American
military buildup in the Gulf and Iraqi threats to shoot down any
U.S. U-2 spy planes flying over Iraq's air space on surveillance
missions.
</P>
<P>
This was the result of intensive diplomatic efforts made by
Aziz, Yeltsin and Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov over
the past two days.
</P>
<P>
Aziz arrived here today from Russia for a two-day visit, during
which he also is expected to hold talks with Egyptian Foreign
Minister Amr Moussa.
</P>
<P>
Aziz's visit is part of his North African tour of Arab
countries to expound Iraq's views on the crisis between Iraq and
the U.N.. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
