<DOCNO> XIE19971120.0078 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iraq Satisfied With Russia-Brokered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Iraq today expressed
satisfaction with the Russian-brokered formula intended to resolve
the Iraq-U.N. crisis by diplomatic means and decided to allow all
the U.N. arms inspectors, including Americans, to return to their
work in Iraq.
</P>
<P>
This was announced in a statement issued following a joint
meeting of Iraq's Revolutionary Command Council and the National
Command of the ruling Baath Party.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that according to the agreement reached
with Russia, the Iraqi leadership decided to invite the
U.N. Special Commission (UNSCOM) on dismantling Iraq's
mass-destruction weapons, with all its members, to return to Iraq
to their work.
</P>
<P>
Also according to the agreement, Russia will in return work for
the lifting of U.N. sanctions on Iraq, which ban Iraq from
exporting its oil.
</P>
<P>
The standoff between Iraq and the U.N. lasted about three weeks
after Iraq on October 29 refused to allow the American arms
inspectors working with the UNSCOM to enter the sites the
commission wanted to inspect.
</P>
<P>
The statement affirmed that Iraq has implemented all the
relevant U.N. Security Council resolutions, including those which
call for eliminating mass-destruction weapons and laboratories
considered by the Americans to have served double purposes or to be
capable of rendering such services.
</P>
<P>
The statement added that Iraq stood united and won the support
of Arab countries, governments and peoples. Its attitude, of
compelling the U.S. to resort to diplomatic channels for a
solution to the crisis, met with understanding from wide circles
all over the world, it said.
</P>
<P>
The statement reaffirmed that Iraq moved some factories,
laboratories and production lines from their original localities
with the aim of preventing them from being destroyed by a possible
U.S. military attack on Iraq. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
