<HEADLINE> Finnish Unemployment Rate Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Finland's unemployment rate
dropped to 13.1 percent at the end of October from 14.8 percent a
year earlier, according to the latest statistics.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the month, the country had 324,000 registered
jobless workers, or 50,000 people less than in the corresponding
time last year.
</P>
<P>
Most of the added jobs were created by the building and
transport sectors.
</P>
<P>
The drop in unemployment rate was attributed to the economic
growth and a series of government measures to create more jobs.
