<HEADLINE> Chen Muhua Meets Maldivian Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MALE, the Maldives, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Chen Muhua, vice
chairperson of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress (NPC) of China, held talks here today with Maldivian
Parliament Speaker Abdulla Hameed.
</P>
<P>
Chen said the traditional friendship between the Chinese people
and the Maldivian people has been further enhanced on the basis of
the Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence ever since the two
countries established diplomatic ties in 1972.
</P>
<P>
She expressed the belief that her current trip will serve to
further promote the understanding between the two peoples and
consolidate the exchange and cooperation between the NPC and the
Maldivian parliament.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, Hameed briefed Chen on the daily work of the
Maldivian parliament.
</P>
<P>
Chen arrived here this morning on a three-day official goodwill
visit as guest of the Maldivian parliament.
</P>
<P>
The Maldives is the last leg of Chen's four-nation South Asia
tour, which already took her to Pakistan, Nepal and Sri Lanka.
</P>
</TEXT>
