<HEADLINE> Allied Signal Establishes Xiamen Maintenance Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Allied Signal, a leading U.S.
manufacturer of aviation equipment, automobile parts and
machinery, has established a maintenance plant in Xiamen, a
special economic zone in China's coastal Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Allied Signal and a local aircraft engineering company
established the plant at a cost of 13 million US dollars. The
plant will specialize in the maintenance of aircraft parts and
overhauls, and will develop into China's maintenance center for
Allied Signal and its partners.
</P>
<P>
The plant, which entered trial operations last March, has been
granted a maintenance certificate by the Civil Aviation
Administration of China (CAAC).
</P>
<P>
Allied Signal, which has invested 150 million US dollars in
nine projects in Shanghai, Nanjing, Guangzhou and Suzhou, plans to
establish three additional cooperative projects in China during
1998. 
