president was conveyed the view point of the government with
regard to the latest situation and the Contempt of Court
(Amendment) Act 1997.
</P>
<P>
Asked whether the government would impeach the president,
Abbasi said, "We would wait for some time." He said the
prevailing situation is very tense.
</P>
<P>
The Parliament would be discussing the situation, he said. The
Parliament is confident of resolving the crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Parliamentary party meeting of the PML and its allied
parties held a meeting this evening which was chaired by Prime
Minister Nawaz Sharif. The meeting was reported to have reached a
"consensus".
</P>
<P>
Abbasi, the only government spokesman who talked to the press
at the end of the meeting, said members of the National Assembly
have reached a "consensus" on the situation, adding that "we have
to wait for sometime for using our option."
</P>
<P>
Replying to a question, he said the consensus may be further
discussed.
</P>
<P>
Abbasi expressed the confidence that the Parliament will
overcome the prevalent crisis.  
</P>
