<HEADLINE> Seminar on Effects of Single Currency of EU Held in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 20 (Xinhua) -- China Minsheng Banking
Corporation and Credit Commercial De France held a seminar in
Shanghai today, to discuss the effects of the single currency of
European Union upon global economy and trade.
</P>
<P>
European Union will start using European Dollar, the only
currency among its member states from January 1, 1999. And this
will effect the present international monetary market and global
trade.
</P>
<P>
Financial risks do exist during the transition period for EU
member states towards the single currency system, and precautions
should be made against the risks, according to financial experts
attending the seminar.
</P>
<P>
China Minsheng Banking Corporation is the country's first
share-holding bank and mainly serves the non-state economic sector.
</P>
<P>
The Credit Commercial De France, one of the five largest
commercial banks in France, has opened a representative office in
Shanghai. It is seeking for possibility to establish a branch bank
in China.
</P>
<P>
It is said that the two banks will start cooperation in foreign
exchange and other international banking business right after the
seminar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
