<DOCNO> XIE19971120.0100 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU to Aid Tunisia for Rural Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, November 20 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission today
approved a grant of 50 million ECU (56 million U.S. dollars) to
Tunisia for rural development and natural resource management.
</P>
<P>
The aid is directed to development and management projects in
eight provinces of northern and central Tunisia. It is aimed at
even out regional disparities.
</P>
<P>
Tunisia's agricultural sector employs about one-third of the
working population of the country but contributes only 13.7 percent
to the country's gross domestic product. The income of
agricultural households is well below non-agricultural incomes.
</P>
<P>
The EU aid will boost the incomes of disadvantaged rural
population and improve their living conditions.
</P>
<P>
The European Union has made an accumulated contribution of some
73 million ECU (83 million dollars) to the national rural
development policy in the northern African country.
</P>
<P>
Since 1996, the EU has given financial assistance to Tunisia in
the form of grants and loans totalling 294 million ECU (335 million
dollars) to help the country strengthen its economic transition.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971120.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-20 </DATE_TIME>
