<HEADLINE> Shenyang Small State-Owned Enterprises on Sale </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Shenyang, the capital of
Liaoning Province and the largest industrial city in Northeast
China, has auctioned shares in 192 small state- and
collectively-owned enterprises, and sold 12 state-owned
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The more than 3,000 people attending this morning's auction
included representatives from nongovernmental enterprises,
corporations and individuals. Buyers will be guaranteed priority
in terms of capital transfers, debt reconciliation, land leases
and placement of employees, according to city officials.
</P>
<P>
Shenyang Mayor Mu Suixin said that sales of small enterprises
represent the first step in the reform of enterprise ownership.
</P>
<P>
He said enterprises placed on the auction block came from nine
sectors, including the machine-building, pharmaceutical,
metallurgical, electronics, textile and chemical sectors.
</P>
<P>
Shenyang has introduced ownership reform to 1,128 enterprises,
or 29 percent of total enterprises in the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
