<HEADLINE> Israel Tightens Security in East Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, November 20 (Xinhua) -- The Israeli government
today ordered the military and police to beef up security in East
Jerusalem following the shooting incident Wednesday night which
killed one Jewish student and injured another.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu announced that the order
was issued this morning after urgent consultations with key
cabinet members and the military and police leaders.
</P>
<P>
In the shooting incident near the Damascus Gate of East
Jerusalem's Old City, one Jewish student was killed on the spot
and another was seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
The injured was operated overnight at the Hadassah Hospital and
is now in a critical condition, according to sources of the
hospital.
</P>
<P>
The two students were on their way home after finishing their
studies when gunmen opened fire at short range.
</P>
<P>
So far, no one has claimed responsibility for the shooting, but
Israeli police said the suspects could be anti-Israel Muslim
militants.
</P>
<P>
Israeli police and security forces are conducting a
man-hunting for the suspects.
</P>
<P>
This was the first terror attack since the July 30 and
September 4 suicide bombing attacks in two Jerusalem's central
markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
