<HEADLINE> Central China Expects Economic Upsurge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, November 20 (Xinhua) -- A seminar on economic
development strategies for central China in the early 21st century
was held today in Wuhan, capital of Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was jointly sponsored by China Academy of Social
Sciences, Hubei Provincial Committee of Communist Party of China
(CPC) and Hubei Provincial government. Representatives from
government departments and economists presented the first-ever
theoretical basis for treating the five provinces in central China
as a promising economic zone.
</P>
<P>
Some 140 economists and government officials attended the
seminar, including Jia Zhijie, secretary of the Hubei Provincial
Committee of the CPC, Anhui provincial Governor Hui Liangyu,
Jiangsu Governor Shu Shengyou, Li Chengyu, deputy governor of
Henan Province, and He Tongxin, deputy governor of Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
Economists and officials in attendance expressed confidence in
the prospects for rapid economic growth in the five central
provinces over the next 15 years. They called for the provinces to
concentrate on becoming "economic powerhouses in China".
</P>
<P>
Said provinces have pledged to join in a coordinated effort to
accelerate economic development.  
</P>
