forum. He noted that Chinese President Jiang Zemin has sent a
congratulatory message praising the forum and that Premier Li Peng
has met with senior foreign participants.
</P>
<P>
Keating expressed delight in having the opportunity to attend
the forum, and pointed to the fact that environmental protection
is an issue of major importance.
</P>
<P>
Liu Huaqiu, director of the Foreign Affairs Office of the State
Council, also attended today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
Over 100 international environmentalists and dignitaries,
including Keating, former Dutch Prime Minister R.F.N. Lubbers, and
representatives from major western industrial and financial firms
are attending the forum which will close tomorrow.  
</P>
</TEXT>
