<DOCNO> XIE19971120.0110 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Intl. Symposium on Clean Coal Technology Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, November 20 (Xinhua) -- A three-day international
symposium on clean coal technology closed today in Xiamen, a port
in east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Some 230 representatives from 16 countries and regions, the
World Bank, and a large number of transnational companies attended
the symposium sponsored by the Chinese Ministry of
Energy, the U.S. Department of Energy, and the Energy
Administration of the European Commission.
</P>
<P>
Participants held in-depth discussions on wide-ranging issues,
including macro development strategies concerning clean coal
technology, coal processing, coal conversion, pollution control
and treatment of waste materials.
</P>
<P>
"Clean coal technology" is a general term referring to all
techniques used to improve efficiency and reduce environmental
pollution in the process of developing and using coal.
</P>
<P>
Coal is one of China's major sources of primary energy, with
annual coal production and consumption accounting for some 75
percent of the nation's total primary energy output and energy
consumption volume.
</P>
<P>
China's recent introduction of clean coal technology
applications has resulted from an overseas research cooperation
project for the direct liquefaction of coal. The construction of
large industrial clean coal demonstration project will be
completed prior to the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government attaches great importance to the
development of clean coal technology and has placed related
development on its agenda for the next century. The developmental
goals for clean coal technology will be to protect the environment
and promote economic development.
</P>
<P>
A leading group focusing on the development and promotion of
clean coal technology was formed in 1995. The group consists of
representatives from industries, and related efforts are being
carried out under the auspices of the State Planning Commission.
</P>
<P>
The "China Clean Coal Technology Agenda for the Ninth
Five-Year-Plan Period (1996-2000) and Development Outlines for the
Year 2010," compiled by experts from various fields, was approved
by the State Council in June 1996. Relevant departments are also
actively drafting their own clean coal technology development
plans.
</P>
<P>
China has established exchange and cooperation ties related to
clean coal technology with related United Nations organizations
and industrialized nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971120.0111 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poland Strives to Intensify Cooperation with HK: Polish President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Poland is striving to
intensify and accelerate its cooperation with Hong Kong, Polish
President Aleksander Kwasniewski said here today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a luncheon hosted by the Hong Kong Trade Development
Council (TDC), Kwasniewski, who arrived in Hong Kong this morning
for a two-day visit as the last leg of his week-long state visit
to China, extended his welcome to Hong Kong investors.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong, a major financial center of the Far East, is a place
where many international trade routes intersect. It is a town
which links traditional Chinese values and the technology which
belongs to the 21st century, Kwasniewski said.
</P>
<P>
"Polish machines and equipment, Polish technology can go to
China via Hong Kong. A broad stream of Chinese goods is already
flowing to Poland via Hong Kong," the Polish president said.
</P>
<P>
"We want to do all we can to make Hong Kong also an open gate
for Polish exports destined for China," he said. "We are looking
for new markets, new cooperation possibilities," he added.
</P>
<P>
"We do want to restore the economic relations with Far-Eastern
markets, especially those of China, which were strained at the
beginning of 1990s," Kwasniewski said.
</P>
<P>
Victor Fung, chairman of the TDC, delivered a welcome speech at
the luncheon, stressing that Hong Kong regards Poland as a base
toward East Europe. Poland is now Hong Kong's second largest
trading partner in East Europe.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) of China, will host an official
banquet in honor of the Polish president this evening at the
Government House.
</P>
<P>
Kwasniewski started his visit to China on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Kwasniewski held talks with President Jiang Zemin and other
Chinese leaders in Beijing. He also visited Shanghai in the east
and Shenzhen in the south. 
</P>
</TEXT>
