<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Envisages Financial System for Market Economy (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As China continues to develop a market economy, financial
activities penetrate every part of society and the economy and the
financial sector is playing an increasingly important role in
macro-control. So, safe, highly-efficient and stable financial
operations are essential for the sustained and healthy development
of the national economy.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, China has maintained the sound momentum in
economic growth, effectively curbing inflation while keeping the
rapid economic growth. While the economic situation gets better
year by year, financial reforms have made advances and the
financial sector has continued to open up.
</P>
<P>
It has implemented the guidelines of the CPC Central Committee
and the State Council and has done a great deal in keeping an
adequately tight monetary policy, strengthening and improving
macro-economic controls, standardizing financial order, increasing
supervision, and eliminating hidden financial risks.
</P>
<P>
These have played an important role in preventing an overheated
economy, controlling inflation, restructuring the economy,
promoting overall reforms, opening-up, and development, and
maintaining social stability.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
