<HEADLINE> Value of HK Manufacturers' Orders Rises in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 20 (Xinhua) -- The value of Hong Kong
manufacturers' orders-on-hand for local production in September
increased by two percent over a year earlier, according to
official statistics released today.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the same month of last year, increases in the
value of orders were recorded in the printing and publishing
industry, the electronic products industry and the textiles
industry.
</P>
<P>
However, decreases in the value of orders were recorded in the
plastic products industry, the fabricated metal products industry,
the electrical products industry and the wearing apparel industry.
</P>
<P>
Manufacturers' orders-on-hand refer to orders and parts of
orders received earlier by manufacturers for local production
which remain unfilled at the end of the reference month.  
</P>
</TEXT>
