<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Meeting Between Angolan President, UNITA Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Angolan President Eduardo dos
Santos has said that his meeting with the opposition leader Jonas
Savimbi expected to take place at the end of this month will be
postponed, the Angola News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Angolan reporters at a hospital in
Brazil, President dos Santos said that he had undertaken an
operation on his heel on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
After being discharged from hospital three or four days later,
he has to stay in Brazil for another 15 days under the care
of doctors, the president added.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the planned summit between him and the National
Union for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA) leader Savimbi
has to be postponed, said dos Santos.
</P>
<P>
The president further said that he will fix a new date for the
summit through consultations as soon as he returns to Luanda
early December.
</P>
<P>
This will be the fifth meeting between the leaders of the two
Angolan warring sides since the Lusaka peace agreement was signed
in 1994 and also the first one to be held in their own country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
