<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senior Official Reiterates "One China" Principle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 20 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official
reiterated today that the Communist Party of China and Chinese
people will stand firm on the "one China" principle and resolutely
oppose any attempts to split China.
</P>
<P>
In an address to the Sixth National Conference of the All-China
Federation of Taiwan Compatriots which opened today in Beijing,
State Councillor Lou Gan said that Chinese leader Jiang Zemin's
report to the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) clearly outlined the promotion of peaceful
reunification as one of the major tasks facing the CPC and Chinese
people.
</P>
<P>
He said the report clearly stipulated that the realization of
China's ultimate reunification is a great historic mission of the
Chinese Communist Party, and reiterated that China will
steadfastly adhere to the principles of "peaceful reunification"
and "one country, two systems".
</P>
<P>
The report called for formal talks to end hostilities between
the two sides under the principle of "one China", and urged Taiwan
authorities to earnestly table suggestions and proposals,
according to Lou, who also serves as a member of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
"The report clearly exhibited our confidence and determination
to solve the Taiwan issue and realize the country's ultimate
reunification," said Lou, adding that the report will exert great
influence on promoting peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
Lou pointed out that the development of splittist trends in
Taiwan and interference on the part of foreign hostile forces have
seriously impeded the reunification process. "There is still a
difficult task in opposing splittism and Taiwan independence,"
said Lou.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that China will act in the spirit of the 15th
Party congress, unswervingly adhere to the "one China" principle
and firmly oppose any activities designed to split China,
including calls for "Taiwan independence", "two Chinas" and "one
China, one Taiwan".
</P>
<P>
"We firmly oppose any interference from foreign forces, and any
attempts to use 'referendums' to alter the fact that Taiwan is an
inseparable part of China", said Lou, adding that "China will
never allow an outside force to change Taiwan's status as an
inseparable part of China."
</P>
<P>
He called for increased economic, cultural and personnel
exchanges, and the timely realization of direct postal, commercial
and transportation links between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
"We sincerely hope that traditionally patriotic Taiwan people
will join hands with us to promote reunification," said Lou.
</P>
<P>
He said the All-China Federation of Taiwan Compatriots is an
important force for developing relations between the two sides and
promoting the cause of peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
Lou expressed hope that the new leadership elected during the
current meeting will join in fulfilling the historic mission of
national reunification and making new contributions to the great
cause. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
