<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Announces Border Travel Regulations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 20 (Xinhua) -- China has come out with
interim regulations for fast-growing border tourism.
</P>
<P>
Under the new regulations, organizations and individuals must
get approval before getting involved in border tourism or
expanding the business scale of border tourism.
</P>
<P>
The regulations also ban public-funded border travel, prohibit
travelers from overstaying or engaging in illegal emigration, and
provide that visa arrangements should be made within localities of
one's registered permanent residence.
</P>
<P>
The document, which is in 16 articles, also clearly defines the
meaning of border tourism and its responsible departments, the
prerequisites for opening a border tourism business, the main
contents of an agreement signed with travel organizations of
neighboring countries, and procedures for opening a border tourism
organization.
</P>
<P>
There are also terms concerning the way a Chinese citizen can
participate in border travel and methods of dealing with
law-breakers.
</P>
<P>
The document was jointly issued by the National Tourism
Administration of China, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the
Ministry of Public Security, and the General Administration of
Customs. The purpose of the document is to further open China's
tourism sector to the outside world, enhance the economic
prosperity and social stability in border areas, and improve
management of border tourism, according to a spokesman for the
national tourism administration.
</P>
<P>
A campaign will be launched to ensure the implementation of the
new regulations, the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
