<HEADLINE> Nigeria Remains Food Basket of Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, November 20 (Xinhua) -- A senior Nigerian agricultural
official has said that Nigeria has attained a high level of food
security in the past two decades and that it can still boast of
being the Food Basket of Africa.
</P>
<P>
The head of the Federal Agricultural Coordinating Unit, Salisu
Ingawa, said in Abuja at the weekend that there has never been a
food crisis in Nigeria in the last 20 to 23 years.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria's importation of rice does not mean that it could not
produce enough food to feed the population, he said, adding that
Nigeria has been exporting food to neighboring countries such as
Cameroun, Togo and the Niger Republic.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that his organization has mapped out strategies
for attaining greater heights in food production from the next
farming season.
</P>
<P>
Such strategies, he said, involve the strengthening of the
research-input-farmer linkage through state agricultural
development programs with a view to enlightening farmers on
modern and more productive system of farming.  
</P>
</TEXT>
