<HEADLINE> Enterprise Group in Northeastern China (With Correction in Para 6) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, November 20 (Xinhua) -- A large-scale cement
enterprise group, composed of five state-owned enterprises, is
scheduled to formally start business by the end of the year in
northeastern China's Liaoning Province, a traditional center of
heavy industry.
</P>
<P>
Local statistics show that the province has more than 300
cement works, including 38 state-owned large and medium cement
firms, with a total annual output of 18 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Sources said the new cement group has a combined designed
capacity of 5 million tons of cement a year, with a total net
assets of 1.78 billion yuan (about 222 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Experts said the new cement group will be more competitive in
domestic and overseas markets.
</P>
<P>
Once the group begins operations, its profits are expected to
increase by 100 million yuan (about 12 million US dollars) in
comparison to profits of the original five cement works.
</P>
<P>
The group is expected to produce eight (rpt. eight) million
tons of cement annually and gain more than 5 billion yuan (about
625 million U.S. dollars) in annual sales by the end of 2000,
which would rank first in the country.
</P>
<P>
The group is expected to become the largest cement producer
in the country in 2010.  
</P>
</TEXT>
