<HEADLINE> Lebanon Sets up National Employment Bureau </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese Labor Ministry
has set up the National Employment Bureau (NEB) in a bid to
improve employment, local newspaper Daily Star reported today.
</P>
<P>
The ministry's Director-General Rateb Saliba explained that the
bureau will provide information on market needs and capabilities,
function as a guidance to training and rehabilitation and an
employment mechanism.
</P>
<P>
As a bridge to link establishments and job seekers, it will
classify and specify different sorts of jobs to facilitate the
entire procedure, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The NEB's basic objectives are to connect the labor market
with vocational and other education, guide first-time job
seekers, and prepare for them to enter the job market," the
ministry's consultant Jamal Fakhoury told the daily.
</P>
<P>
Saliba called on companies, employers and job seekers to place
trust in the work of the bureau to help it play an active role in
promoting employment. 
</P>
