<HEADLINE> China Envisages Financial System for Market Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 20 (Xinhua) -- China will strive to establish
a financial system that meets the requirements of the development
of a socialist market economy within three years, according to a
national financial conference which ended here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The system will cover financial institutions, markets and
supervision, according to the three-day conference organized by
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and
the State Council.
</P>
<P>
China must significantly raise the operational and management
levels of its financial sector, improve the national financial
order, ward off financial risks, and increase its ability to
prevent and counter financial risks. These steps must be taken to
create the right conditions for further reforms, opening-up and
modernization.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin, General Secretary of the CPC Central Committee,
Premier Li Peng and Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji made important
speeches at the meeting. Hu Jintao and Li Lanqing, both members of
the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee, also attended the meeting. 
</P>
