<HEADLINE> Banda's Condition Improved: Doctor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Former Malawian
President Kamazu Banda has regained consciousness in a hospital
here following treatment for a severe bout of pneumonia, doctors
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Banda's condition had improved since he was admitted to the
hospital Monday in a coma, hospital spokeswoman Imelda Swartz was
quoted by local media as saying.
</P>
<P>
The aging former president was placed on a ventilator to help
him breathe.
</P>
<P>
Banda, believed to be older than his official 91 years, was
found ill at the weekend with pneumonia and high fever. He was
rushed to Johannesburg for emergency treatment.
</P>
<P>
Swartz said Banda's general health appeared to be good, and
doctors expected him to return to Malawi following his
hospitalization.
</P>
<P>
Banda ruled for 30 years after independence before being
ousted in 1994 elections by president Bakili Muluzi. 
