<HEADLINE> Italian Lower House Passes Immigration Bill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Italian Lower House tonight
passed a contentious immigration bill which outlines new rules
governing the expulsion of illegal immigrants and allows for
"unlimited" residency permits after five years.
</P>
<P>
The bill, which now moves on to the Senate for debate, sets out
more severe regulations for expelling immigrants. Those with
criminal records or without valid identification would be
immediately deported if the measure is passed.
</P>
