<HEADLINE> Earthquake Victims In Northwest China Move Into New Houses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, November 20 (Xinhua) -- The earthquake victims in Kashi
County in China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region have all moved
into new houses built with government funds, according to official
sources here.
</P>
<P>
The county has been hit by seven strong earthquakes this year,
measuring six or more on the Richter scale, and over 5,000
aftershocks.
</P>
<P>
"Before the winter began, all the 11,630 families in Kashi
whose houses were destroyed have been resettled in new houses,"
said a local official, and 247 elderly people and 60 orphans have
been moved into five care homes and an orphanage rebuilt after the
quakes.
</P>
<P>
The central and local governments have allotted 43 million yuan
to help the victims restore their homes. 
</P>
