In a press conference held in Iran's northeastern city of
Mashhad, head of the Afghan Ministry of Religious Guidance,
Endowment and the Hajj Khodadad Erfani said that the new
provisional government would rule only for nine months until a
permanent government was elected by the people.
</P>
<P>
Erfani said that the national government of Afghanistan would
be formed within a month under the presidency of Burhanuddin
Rabbani based on understandings reached among various Afghan
political factions.
</P>
<P>
He said that various government posts have been distributed
among all groups and even the Taliban, which ousted the
government led by president Rabbani in September last year.
</P>
<P>
However, it was not clear whether the Taliban leaders in
Kabul had agreed with the decision made by the anti-Taliban
coalition which was formed after Rabbani's government fled the
country's capital of Kabul.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, IRNA said, Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi
Wednesday held a meeting with Rabbani who is currently in Tehran
for medical treatment.
</P>
<P>
Iran believes that a broad-based mutual understanding in
Afghanistan would be the only way to end the crisis in that
war-stricken country, Kharrazi said.
</P>
<P>
He hoped a speedy restoration of peace and tranquillity in
Afghanistan, saying that Iran's policy was always against the
use of any military solution to the Afghan crisis.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of the crisis, Kharrazi said, Iran had
sincerely put all its efforts in trying to positively influence
the political atmosphere in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Iran is fully determined to contribute toward the humanitarian
cause to help bring peace in Afghanistan through a tranquil
diffusion of the current crisis, he added.
</P>
<P>
However, Rabbani said that the warmongers and their foreign
supporters should change their policy to pave the way for
restoration of peace and tranquility in the war-torn
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
