<HEADLINE> Davenport, Seles Out of Chase Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Lindsay Davenport and Monica
Seles, the best two of American top women players, dropped out of
the WTA season-ending event Chase Championships here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Current world No.2 Davenport was outpowered 6-2, 4-6, 6-7
(7-9) by compatriot Mary Joe Fernandez, and former world No.1
player Seles was ousted by Spaniard Arantxa Sanchez Vicario 6-3,
4-6, 4-6.
</P>
<P>
Davenport, who was seeded third in the two million
U.S. dollars event, blasted a strong third-set start with a 4-1
lead before Fernandez stormed back to tie at 4-4.
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old Fernandez, who had a 4-3 record in meeting
with Davenport, pulled back on two match points and moved up to
6-5. But she squandered one match point though she won the
first-round match eventually.
</P>
<P>
Davenport, the German Open, also survived three match points
in the tie-breaker to tie at 6-6 before her long-sent forehand
ended the marathon match which last two and a half hours.
</P>
<P>
"It was a great match," Fernandez said. "I made some great
shots at important points. I was very happy with how I played."
</P>
<P>
"I made too many mistakes," Davenport said, "I was not
aggressive enough at the crucial points in the match, especially
in the third set."
</P>
<P>
Fifth-seeded Seles, 23, the title holder of the event in 1990,
1991 and 1992, didn't play the event in the next three year in a
row due to stab wounds.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez, the losing finalist in 1993, has rose to 10-8 career
here, joining already quarter-finalists as Swiss Martina Hingis,
Pierce and Nathalie Tauziat of France, Jana Novotna of the Czech
Republic, Croatia's Iva Majoli and Romanian Irina Spirlea.
</P>
</TEXT>
