<DOCNO> XIE19971120.0195 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Telephones Now Available in Rural Northwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region in northwest China has increased the number of its rural
telephone subscribers from 3,130 to 198,000 during the past five
years.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, telephones are now available in 96
percent of the 832 towns and 38.3 percent of the 8,916 villages.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, this autonomous region had only 56 computer-controlled
telephone switchboard centers for its rural areas. But 86 counties
now have their own computer-controlled telephone systems and even
have such modern telecommunications methods as optical fibers,
microwave transmission and digital techniques. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
