<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Calls for Aid to Flood Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, November 20 (Xinhua) -- International donor
organizations are urged to extend financial and material support
to people affected by flood as a result of the overflowing of
Wabe Shebelle River in Somali State.
</P>
<P>
The Disaster Prevention and Preparedness Commission of
Ethiopia said wednesday that it needs the support of
international welfare organizations and the people in the country
as it has been unable to alleviate those hit by the floods.
</P>
<P>
The commission said that they need food, helicopters, motor
boats, shelters and medicines for the displaced people in Somali
State, according to the Ethiopian News Agency.
</P>
<P>
It said according to meteorological information, continuous
rainfall is expected in Ethiopia and Somalia in the coming weeks
while November and December are destined to face heavy rainfall
because of the El-Nino phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
Efforts are underway to alleviate the problems of food,
shelter and transportation by making use of the commission's
reserve, the commission said, adding that if rainfall continues
in the stated areas more relief food and medical supplies will be
needed as there will be more displaced people and property
damage.
</P>
<P>
The commission also said it will announce soon the number of
needy people in the country and the quantity of relief food
needed. 
</P>
