Quanzhou-Xiamen-Zhangzhou expressway, the Haicang Bridge and
Jiangxi Province's Hengfeng-Nanping railway line topped 23.99
billion yuan (about 3 billion U.S. dollars), accounting for 58.6
percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
The plan calls for a provincial investment of 6.57 billion yuan
(about 820 million U.S. dollars) in 10 projects this year.
</P>
<P>
Quanzhou-Xiamen, involving a total investment of 2.79 billion
yuan (about 348 million U.S. dollars), is scheduled to begin
operations by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Construction of Hengfeng-Nanping railway line, costing 2.43
billion yuan (about 300 million U.S. dollars), is expected to be
completed at the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
The Fuzhou-Quanzhou expressway, with a total investment of 4.67
billion yuan (about 584 million U.S. dollars), is under
construction and should be completed in 1999. 
