<HEADLINE> Heilongjiang Promoting Agricultural Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN November 20 (Xinhua) -- Heilongjiang Province has
launched a major effort to tap its agricultural resources and
rapidly develop its rural economy.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang, an important grain production center in the
country, has concentrated its energy to control flooding in the
eastern portion of the province and drought in the western portion.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show the province has more than 6.67 million
hectares of farmland, 80 percent of which is medium- and low-yield
fields. Ninety percent of the farmland is distributed in the
plains, giving the province ample potential for further
development of its agricultural resources.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 the province transformed 1.46 million hectares of
medium- and low-yield farmland and opened up 280,000 hectares of
wasteland, which increased grain production by six billion
kilograms.
</P>
<P>
The province also has increased its reliance on farm machinery,
improved the variety of grains and modernized cultivation
techniques. 
</P>
