<HEADLINE> Garden City Adds to Green Reputation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, November 20 (Xinhua) -- The reason Hefei has the name of
"National Garden City" is obvious to visitors in this capital city
of east China's Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
The city's grassland coverage rate now stands at 31 percent,
with a per capita acreage of 7.4 square meters. Those figures rank
the city fourth among 35 large and medium-sized cities in the
country.
</P>
<P>
In the downtown area of Hefei, 12 hectares known as "Urban Bird
Island" are covered with trees, attracting thousands of birds
daily.
</P>
<P>
Bird Island is part of an 8.7-kilometer-long garden, covering
an area of 138 hectares which surrounds the city.
</P>
<P>
In the past two years, Hefei planted more than 20,000 trees and
30,000 square meters of grass in this garden, where contains many
famous cultural relics.
</P>
<P>
The city also has built and improved 10 parks and gardens
including a wild animal zoo, a flower-planting center and a garden
street.
</P>
<P>
A 50-kilometer forest belt also is being planted along the
city's Second-ring Road.
</P>
<P>
Open areas, such as parking lots and places along main streets,
have been covered with grass.
</P>
<P>
Hefei, covering 150 square kilometers, has a population of 1.1
million and is one of the 35 major cities in the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
