<HEADLINE> Public Workers Go on Strike in Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, November 19 (Xinhua) -- About one million Venezuelan
employees of the central and decentralized administrations staged
a one-day strike today.
</P>
<P>
It was in support of municipal workers to whom the government
refused to pay compensatory payments stipulated in a contract
signed by the government.
</P>
<P>
The strike was organized by the Federation of Public Workers
(Fedeunep) because the government gave no response to their
demands. It completely paralyzed public administration offices
and institutions, including ministries, hospitals and public
companies.
</P>
<P>
The Fedeunep Secretary, Carlos Borge, said employees in the
public sector are also protesting against alleged violation of the
worker rights in several institutions of the central,
decentralized and regional administrations.
</P>
<P>
The federation demands workers' participation in ongoing reform
of several institutions of public administration. This had been
established in an April-1996 act that was ratified in a contract
signed between Fedeunep and the Labor Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The worker's leader indicated Tuesday that although the workers
would be on strike only today, it could be extended if the
government did not respond to workers' demands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
