<HEADLINE> Ministerial Meeting Urges Iraq to Accept Return of U.N. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Participants attending a
ministrial meeting on the Iraq weapons inspection crisis today
urged Iraq to unconditionally accept the return of the United
Nations inspectors.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministers of the Great Britain, the Russian Federation,
the United States and France and the representative of the
Minister of Foreign Affairs of the People's Republic of China made
the above call in a joint statement issued at the end of a
two-hour ministerial meeting held here.
</P>
