<HEADLINE> Sweden Lashes Out at Israel for Settlement Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Sweden lashed out at Israel
today for the Jewish state's continued establishment of Jewish
settlements in occupied Gaza Strip and West Bank despite mounting
international pressure.
</P>
<P>
In an address delivered at Uppsala University in Stockholm,
Foreign Minister Lena Hjelm-Wallen said that the establishment of
jewish settlements in those regions was in violation of
international law.
</P>
<P>
"An occupation state has no right to move its residents into
the occupied territories. The Israeli government must cease its
provocative settlement policies," she said.
</P>
<P>
No state is entitled to disregard relevant provisions of
international law, the foreign minister reaffirmed.
</P>
<P>
The act of forced occupation of land is unacceptable, she said,
demanding that the Jewish state withdraw from its occupied
territories.
</P>
<P>
Hjelm-Wallen said that Sweden will join the European Union in
promoting the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Appealing for building a justified and lasting peace in the
Middle East, she said that the achievement of this target is
necessitated by the establishment of a Palestinian state.
</P>
<P>
Hjelm-Wallen said the possibility of a final solution to the
Middle East issues was closely related to the establishment of a
Palestinian state.
</P>
<P>
She elaborated on the history and the status quo in Middle East
crisis, and appealed for a break in the deadlock to find some
compromise. 
</P>
