<HEADLINE> Ministerial Meeting on Iraq Begins in Geneva </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, November 20 (Xinhua) -- The ministerial meeting of
delegations from the five permanent members of the United Nations
Security Council began here early today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is aimed at finding a diplomatic solution to the
Iraq weapons inspection crisis.
</P>
<P>
Heading the delegations attending the meeting are Ambassador
Sha Zukang from China's permanent mission in Geneva, British
Foreign Secretary Robin Cook, French Foreign Minister Hubert
Vedrine, Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov and U.S.
Secretary of State Madeleine Albright.
</P>
<P>
During the closed-door meeting, they will discuss a proposal by
Russia, which initiated the meeting. The Russian proposal is said
to contain a solution to the crisis without resorting to force and
reaffirming the authority of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
China, France, Russia, the United Kingdom and the United States
are the five permanent members of the Security Council and each
has the right to veto decisions. 
