<HEADLINE> Asia-Pacific Telecom Meeting to Be Held in Bangkok </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, November 20 (Xinhua) -- The 21th session of the
Management Committee of the Asia-Pacific Telecommunity (APT) will
be held in the Thai capital of Bangkok on November 24-28.
</P>
<P>
Participants will include telecommunication executives from the
government and private sectors of various Asia-pacific nations.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will review the progress of work undertaken by the
APT this year and decide the annual budget and work program of the
APT for 1998, a local newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
The APT was set up under an inter-government agreement in 1979.
Over the years, it has emerged as the leading telecommunication
entity of the region, contributing to the development of
telecommunication in the region.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the APT has 29 members, four associate members and
35 affiliate members. In addition, several private companies take
part in APT activities as participating companies.  
