<HEADLINE> Myanmar Builds More Bridges to Link Capital, Regions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Four more bridges are being
built to link the Myanmar capital of Yangon with surrounding areas
as well as states and divisions to speed up the flow of
commodities.
</P>
<P>
Official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar said today the four
bridges of Maha Bandoola, Ngamoeyeik, Shwepyitha and Aungzeya,
whose lengths range from 236 meters to 570 meters, are to connect
Yangon with Dawbon, Shwepyitha and Hlaingtharya as well as states
and divisions.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the four bridges are expected to be completed
in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, two major bridges across Myanmar's Ayeyarwady River
have also been under construction to cut short the travel time
between its eastern and western banks. Another two bridges over
the river have been inaugurated.  
</P>
