<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Garment Group Company Set Up in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 20 (Xinhua) -- The China National Garments
Corp. and the Chinese National Garment Research and Design Center
have combined into a single company as part of the country's
effort to restructure its state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The new firm, the China Garment Group Company, expects to
utilize the best of the two former companies and to improve
technological development and production. The merger also is
expected to boost the country's garment industry.
</P>
<P>
China National Garments Corp. was set up in 1984 and played an
important role in organizing the country's clothing production and
attracting foreign businesses.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese National Garment Research and Design Center was
established in 1982 and became a center of technological service
for the industry as well as a match-maker for the Chinese garment
industry and overseas counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Along with the speedy development of the its economy, China's
textile industry will be upgraded and the country's traditional
garment industry shifted its growth mode from quantity to quality.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese garment industry badly needs new controls, experts
say, which would improve the product mix of domestic garment
markets and increase export prices.
</P>
<P>
The new company had 874 million yuan in total assets as of
September this year, with net assets accounting for 348 million
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The company has set a goal of 2 billion yuan in annual sales by
2000 as well as 2 billion yuan in assets in the year.
</P>
<P>
By the turn of the century, China's domestic demand for
clothing is expected to reach 5.57 billion pieces worth 360
billion U.S. dollars. The country is expected to produce 10
billion pieces of clothing a year, with imports reaching 1 billion
U.S. dollars and exports reaching 35 billion U.S. dollars by
2000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
