<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia's GNP Growth to Reach Seven Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavia's gross national
product (GNP) growth rate this year will be seven percent, the
Yugoslavia Economic Federation said today.
</P>
<P>
In a symposium held here, the federation also said price hikes
will be controlled at 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the first nine months, the country's foreign trade
volume was 5.7 billion U.S. dollars. Exports rose by 29 percent
while imports increased by 16 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the period, per-capita income skyrocketed by 22.3
percent compared with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The federation estimated the GNP growth in 1998 would be 10
percent.
</P>
<P>
The federation urged the government to maintain the sustained
economic policy in 1998, which was adopted in recent years.
</P>
