<HEADLINE> Anti-Corruption Accord Takes Effect in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Argentine President
Carlos Menem announced here that the Inter-American Agreement
Against Corruption took effect in Argentina as of Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Menem said that the accord is one of the most outstanding
international achievements in the subject of public ethics, and
that the agreement will turn out to be an important juridical
weapon to curb corruption.
</P>
<P>
The 28-article agreement is a juridical accord for hemispheric
cooperation aimed at preventing government officials from
practicing corruption. Iberian American countries will take joint
actions to fulfill that goal.
</P>
<P>
Argentina was one of the first signatories of the agreement,
which was initialed during the Miami Presidential Summit in the
United States in 1994 and approved in the city of Caracas,
Venezuela, in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
