<BODY>
<HEADLINE> El Nino Claims 16 Lives in Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, November 19 (Xinhua) -- At least 16 people have been
killed and thousands left homeless in Ecuador as a result of the
climatic phenomenon of "El Nino" over the past 10 days.
</P>
<P>
El Nino also caused about 13 million U.S. dollars in losses in
agriculture and the shrimp industry.
</P>
<P>
Most of the people were killed in the town of Santa Rosa, in
El Oro province, when rivers flooded 80 percent of the residental
areas and left more than 8600 people stranded.
</P>
<P>
Nine of the dead were washed away by the swollen rivers and
some were killed by a water and mud avalanche. Storms took two
lives when lightning struck a cable which burnt the victims.
</P>
<P>
The rising rivers and heavy rains have damaged about 600
hectares of fields and shrimp pond areas in the provinces of El
Oro, Manabi, Guayas, Esmeraldas and Los Rios. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
