<HEADLINE> Ford Pondering Vehicle Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Strategic growth will be the
top priority for Ford Motor Co. as the auto maker establishes its
car-production project in China.
</P>
<P>
"We are confident of being well prepared to produce passenger
vehicles in China," said Vaughn Koshkarian, president of Ford
China operations.
</P>
<P>
He made the announcement on Tuesday during a gathering in
Beijing, launching the company's 44 authorized service centers and
the inauguration of its first service training center.
</P>
<P>
The after-sales service network will target Ford products --
including imported vehicles and the pending China Transit, a
commercial passenger vehicle manufactured in China with Jiangling
Motors Corp (JMC).
</P>
<P>
Ford will continue establishing service training centers in
Shanghai, Guangzhou and Nanchang.
</P>
<P>
Last month, Ford signed a 250 million U.S. dollars worth of
50/50-engine joint venture agreement with Yuejin Motors Group Corp.
The plant will manufacture a range of multivalve engines, between
1.8 liters and 2.3 liters.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
