<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> President Frei Calls for Gender Equality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Chilean President Eduardo
Frei today called for removing obstacles blocking equality between
men and women.
</P>
<P>
Job opportunities for women are still scarce in Chile, even
though women constitute 30 percent of the national labor force,
Frei said today while addressing the Seventh Regional Conference
on Women's Integration into Social and Economic Development in
Latin America and the Caribbean.
</P>
<P>
The participants discussed women's access to decision-making,
power sharing and feasible measures to combat poverty.
</P>
<P>
The three-day forum has attracted more than one hundred
representatives from countries in the Santiago-based Economic
Commission for Latin America and the Caribbean (ECLAC).
</P>
<P>
The ECLAC's Secretary Executive Gert Rosenthal and the Director
of Chile's National Service for Women Josefina Bilba attended the
opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The first Regional Conference on Women took place in Cuba in
1977 and the latest was held in Argentina in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
