<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Has Good Harvest This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, November 19 (Xinhua) -- The harvest of corn in
Romania is expected to reach 12 million tons this year, setting a
record for the past seven years, the Romanian news agency ROMPRES
today quoted the agricultural ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
So far this year, the country has gathered 11.9 million tons of
corn. The harvest of corn last year was 9.6 million tons, the
agency said.
</P>
<P>
The amount of wheat harvested this year so far has reached 7.13
million tons, 3.97 million tons more than last year. The amount of
sugarbeets harvested has reached 2.65 million tons, 20,000 tons
less than last year.
</P>
<P>
The reason for Romania's bumper havest this year is credited to
good cooperation and joint efforts between the government and the
country's farmers. The weather in Romania was reportedly not ideal
this year: the temperatures were lower in spring, and it rained
more often in the summer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
