<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Chinese Hold Concert in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 20 (Xinhua) -- Five established overseas
Chinese composers returned to their homeland and for a concert
here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time the five composers performed such a
concert, featuring both traditional Chinese music and Western
works.
</P>
<P>
The five are Sheng Zongliang, Qu Xiaosong, Chen Qigang, Chen Yi
and Xu Suya, all international music competition winners.
</P>
<P>
They first established their fame in China in the 1980s before
going abroad. Currently they are among the most well-known Chinese
composers living in foreign countries, and their works have been
played by famous symphony orchestras in the United States, France
and Italy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
