<HEADLINE> Germany Donates Locomotives to Bosnian Serbs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, November 19 (Xinhua) -- The German government today
donated five diesel locomotives and 10 carriages to the Republika
Srpska (RS), the Tanjug news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
German railways director Klaus Ebeling and the RS
Transportation Minister Nedeljk Lajic attended the presentation
ceremony in Doboj. A railway line between Doboj and Petrovo was
officially put into use on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ebeling said he hopes that Bosnian railway lines will be
integrated with the European railway network. He said the German
government will present another 40 railroad cars to Bosnian Serbs
in the near future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
