<HEADLINE> Milosevic Turns Down Napoli </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Aston Villa's Yugoslavian
international striker Savo Milosevic has turned down the offer of
struggling Italy's serie A club Napoli, a report said.
</P>
<P>
"I would rather stay here than join a club in Italy who are
struggling," Milosevic was quoted as saying on Wednesday in
Birminghan, England.
</P>
<P>
"That is why I turned down Perugia last season and this is the
same situation.
</P>
<P>
"If I ever go to Italy I would want to join a bigger club," he
added.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the Italian club had set up a meeting with Villa
chairman Doug Ellis negotiating on the transfer.
</P>
<P>
But the meeting was called off for an apparent gap of their
bits and the terms of payment on the striker.
</P>
<P>
Milosevic, former Partizan Belgrade star, moved to Villa in the
1995-96 season with 21 goals in 67 league matches in the last two
season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
