<DOCNO> XIE19971120.0322 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Woman Gives Birth to Septuplets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 19 (Xinhua) -- An Iowa seamstress today
gave birth to four boys and three girls, only the second set of
septuplets ever known to be born alive, The Associated Press
reported.
</P>
<P>
The seven babies were successfully delivered in just six
minutes with the assistance from a medical team of more than 40
specialists. The babies were weighed from two pounds, five ounces
to three pounds, four ounces.
</P>
<P>
The mother was Bobbi McCaughey, 29, of Carlisle. She was in her
31st week of pregnancy. Mrs. McCaughey's due date was mid-January,
but she had been hospitalized since October 15 and the early
delivery was decided Tuesday night because of the number of
babies.
</P>
<P>
It was the first septuplets born in the United States since
May 1985 in Orange, California. In the last set birth, one was
stillborn, three died within 19 days of birth and the remaining
three had medical and developmental problems.
</P>
<P>
There are no known surviving sets of septuplets in the world. A
Saudi Arabian woman gave birth to septuplets in September, but six
died, according to hospital officials there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
