<HEADLINE> IDB Okays Financing for Child Care in Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, November 19 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of a 45
million U.S. dollar loan to help expand and upgrade day-care
services for children under six years of age in Ecuador.
</P>
<P>
The IDB resources will finance training for both parents and
personnel attending the centers as well as instructional
materials.
</P>
<P>
The physical structure of approximately 1,800 day care centers
will be rehabilitated, and a special fund will be set up to
finance both government and nongovernment organizations that
intend to provide new or additional day-care services.
</P>
<P>
The program is designed to benefit low-income groups and to
encourage local communities, civil society, and private
organizations to assume more responsibility for the provision of
day-care services. 
