<HEADLINE> Iraq Concerned With Efforts to End Standoff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, November 19 (Xinhua) -- Iraq is concerned with the
lastest developments in Russia's effort to find a way out of the
present standoff between Baghdad and the U.N. without resorting
to military operations.
</P>
<P>
The official Iraq News Agency reported today that President
Saddam Hussein presided over a Cabinet meeting to review efforts
in solving the crisis through diplomatic and political means.
</P>
<P>
The report said Saddam briefed his Cabinet members on the
Russian plan to end the showdown, whose details have never been
disclosed.
</P>
<P>
The report did not elaborate on the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, foreign ministers of Russia, Britain, France and the
United States are headed for an extraordinary meeting in Geneva to
decide whether the Russian plan will work in persuading Saddam to
reverse his decision and steering clear of a military conflict.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
